text: State Route 619 (SR 619) is an east-west state highway in the northeastern quadrant of the U.S. state of Ohio. The western terminus of State Route 619 is at an interchange with the Interstate 76/U.S. Route 224 freeway in Barberton. Its eastern terminus is at State Route 183 in Lexington Township, just north of Alliance. ==Route description== State Route 619 travels through Summit and Stark Counties. There are no stretches of the route that are incorporated within the National Highway System. ==History== First designated in 1937, SR 619 has generally followed the Barberton-to-Alliance alignment that it maintains today since its inception. With the exception of some minor re- alignments in Barberton, the highway has not seen any other significant changes since making its first appearance. ==Major intersections== ==References== 619 Category:Transportation in Summit County, Ohio Category:Transportation in Stark County, Ohio
